We have OD green and black receivers in stock and ready to ship. Cavalry Arms is no longer making these lowers, so get one before they're gone!

Price does not include shipping to your FFL.  WV residents will need to add 6% sales tax.

http://i477.photobucket.com/albums/rr136/efillc/guns/Picture203.jpg

SPECIAL OFFER!

Custom engraving is available for all purchasers.
For just $25 we will custom engrave your lower so that in the future you can register it on an ATF Form 1 as a short-barrelled rifle.

We are happy to ship to CA and these are legal with a bullet button. We do not charge extra for CC's. We wait two weeks for personal checks to clear before shipping to your FFL. All sales final. Please visit us online at http://www.ExtremeFirepower.com/ and check out our custom rifle builds!

For the folks unfamiliar with a Cavalry Arms lower:

These receivers are injection molded from glass filled nylon 6, a polymer material very similar to that used by other firearms companies. Polymer offers unsurpassed corrosion resistance, finish durability. and is significantly lighter than aluminum based receivers.

They are molded in two halves and assembled using a linear vibration welding process. Linear vibration welding forms the two halves into one solid piece. Every contact surface between the two halves is bonded together with a weld that is even stronger than the parent material.

Injection molding allows for more cost effective and faster production of parts of consistent quality. Production cost savings are passed onto the consumer.

CAV-15 MKII Receiver Features:

    * A1 Length integral Stock (5/8" shorter than A2) with sling loop. 13" Length of Pull.
    * Ergonomically enhanced integral pistol grip
    * Wider magazine well capable of accepting .45 Greasegun magazines with caliber conversion upper receivers and magazine blocks.
    * Standard AR15 magazines can be used without modifications.

title: For Sale:  Glock 17SGT in OD green
postcontent:
Up for sale is a tough to get Glock 17SGT in the OD green frame and 9mm.  Glock has discontinued the OD green frames, so get them while you can!

You're probably asking what the SGT means.  I have no clue and Glock really didn't have an answer for me either, but there are factory upgrades with this G17.  It is not a Gen4 or RTF2 frame.  The frame set-up is identical to that of the Glock 34.

Factory upgrades (Glock parts, installed by Glock at the factory):
Competition trigger package
Rounded smooth wide trigger (not the pyramid step trigger on the G19)
Extended magazine release
Extended slide stop
OD green frame

This was purchased a few months ago to use as a backup to my G34 for IDPA shooting and I decided to get another G34 after having other IDPA folks interpret the weapon failure rule.  It has less than 700 rounds though it and is in excellent condition.

Comes with (2) 17 round mags (Gen3 mags), hard case, loader, paperwork, brush, rod, papers.  If you were to purchase one and try to get these upgrades aftermarket you would find there's about $150-$200 worth of upgrades (parts and labor), add that to the retail price of a Glock 17 and the price could have been as high or higher than $600...obviously I'm not asking that.

$550

I will consider partial trades on this, depending on the item (ammo, other handguns, rifles, shotguns), however I would prefer to sell this outright.

Face to face required.  CCW holders preferred, must have ID and/or CCW in hand at time of transaction.  Due to the BATFE's recent attempts to go after private sellers I now require transfer through a local FFL holder for those who do not have a valid CCW.  If you have a valid CCW permit (out of State is fine w/ valid Missouri ID), you will receive a signed bill of sale from me that you must also sign to protect us both.

title: For Sale:  Remington 870 Competion
postcontent: at first glance this gun looks a lot like a typical 870 Wingmaster, but it is actually the Remington 870 Competition.gun has very nice wood, extended trap forend, 30 inch barrel, and a unique gas operated recoil reduction system housed inside the magazine tube.i was not aware that remington had produced an 870 like this till i happened to stumble onto this one.i did some research and discovered that remington manufactured about 5500 of these guns from 1981-1986 before retiring them.when you consider that Remington has produced more than 10 million 870s, that makes the Competition a pretty rare find!i have only found a few others for sale online and they are listed at up to $700.most of the reviews are very positive with shooters saying that the Competition is a tremendous trap singles gun with very little felt recoil, making it ideal for young, female, or light framed individuals.i am not much of a trap shooter or collector so this gun doesn't really suit my current needs.i have not fired this gun personally, but i did completey disassemble and clean it including the gas system and the trigger assembly so the entire gun is super clean in and out.the finish does show some wear here and there in places typical of a gun this age, most noticably where the forend contacts the left side of the receiver, but overall it is a very beautiful gun!only serious inquiries please, and i am not really looking to trade.i will try to upload pics but if that doesn't work, i would be happy to email them to you.thanks for looking

title: For Sale:  Taurus TCP 738 Stainless Steel .380 New, Unfired
postcontent:
Taurus TCP 738 stainless steel, new unfired.  $260 asking price.   I would work on trade toward  compact .45 1911 style.  The only reason this pistol is for sale, is I ended up with two.  

This pistol comes with all the original equipment: two magazines, two safety keys, carrying case, manual, and box with matching serial number.

If you are looking for a pocket pistol, you need to check this out.  Most .380s operate on the blow back system, which requires a heavy slide and strong recoil spring.  The 738 utilizes the locked breech system like larger caliber pistols, thus the weight can be held to a minimum.  Since it is so light and easy to conceal, mine is with me all the time.  

Taurus tried to make a carrying case to make concealment easier in warm weather.  The black belt case looks like you are carrying a 1970's model calculator.  The pistol fits so nicely in a pocket, that is my carry mode of choice.

Below is from the Taurus web site:

Make way for the lightest Taurus ever created! The 10.2-ounce 738 TCP is not only the lightest semi-auto in the Taurus line; it's lighter than any of our small frame revolvers too! The 738 TCP offers 6+1 shots of .380 ACP, a durable polymer frame and low-profile fixed sights. You have to feel it to believe it!
